         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we derive an a posteriori error bound for the Lagrange-Galerkin discretisation of an unsteady (linear) convection-diffusion problem, assuming only that the underlying space-time mesh is nondegenerate. The proof of this error bound is based on strong stability estimates of an associated dual problem, together with the Galerkin orthogonality of the finite element method. Based on this a posteriori bound, we design and implement the corresponding adaptive algorithm to ensure global control of the error with respect to a user-defined tolerance.</p>
          </abstract>
